<HEADLINE> Scientific Museum to Be Set Up for Zimbabwe's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The National Museums and Monuments
of Zimbabwe in conjunction with the French island of La Reunion is
set to soon establish a scientific and technological museum in the
resort town of Victoria Falls of west Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The museum would be run along the same lines as the Volcano
museum in La Reunion, which focuses on the scientific explanations
about the island's active volcano.
</P>
<P>
Representative of the Volcano museum Phillipe Dupont told the
Zimbabwe News Agency in Bulawayo, Zimbabwe's second largest city,
Monday that the Victoria Falls initiative would center around the
Falls as the central theme.
</P>
<P>
He said the museum would focus on aspects such as water as a
natural element, the rain forest, human and historical content,
the development of art and craft, and environmental protection
among other points of focus.
</P>
<P>
"We envisage the museum to serve as a window for the
development and promotion of the Victoria Falls, and the
partnership and cooperation that will be fostered between Zimbabwe
and La Reunion will be extremely profitable for both countries,"
said Dupont. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
