<HEADLINE> 26 Crewmen Still Missing After Boat Sinks in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six crewmen of the
fishing trawler which sunk off the Eastern Cape coast Saturday
were still missing by late Monday, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
Chances of survival for these crewmen are becoming smaller and
smaller, rescuers were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bad weather in the area hampered rescue efforts Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of nine survivors were plucked from the sea by a
helicopter Sunday. Three bodies were recovered.
</P>
<P>
The South African-registered Palli HJA Mariannu, a 56-meter,
1,000-ton trawler, left Port Elizabeth harbor Saturday morning
with 38 crew members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
