<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Import and Export Declining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' import and export from
January to April this year dropped compared with the same period
in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Data released Monday by Cyprus' Department of Statistics and
Research showed that import fell to 600.1 million pounds (about
1,080.2 million U.S. dollars) in the January-April period from
630.3 million pounds (about 1,134.5 million dollars) in the same
period last year. Export dropped to 153.6 million pounds (276.6
million dollars) from 197.5 million pounds (355.5 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit reached 446.5 million pounds (803.7 million
dollars), compared with 432.8 million pounds (779.0 million
dollars) in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus imported 335.5 million pounds (603.9 million dollars)
worth of goods from the European Union (EU) member states during
the January-April period this year, accounting for 55.9 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the EU member countries imported 36.2 million pounds
(65.2 million dollars) worth of Cyprus' goods, accounting for
54.2 percent of Cyprus's total exports.
</P>
<P>
The Arab countries ranked the second as importer of Cypriot
goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
