<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland Supports Lebanon on Israeli Withdrawal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Polish Foreign Minister Bronislaw
Geremek Monday reiterated his country's support for Lebanon which
demands Israel withdraw from its south without any conditions.
</P>
<P>
"Poland has from the beginning supported the implementation of
the United Nations Resolution 425 and condemned the Israeli
occupation of Lebanese land," Geremek told reporters after meeting
with Lebanese Prime Minister Salim Hoss.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, adopted by the U.N. after the first Israeli
invasion of Lebanon in 1978, calls for a unconditional Israeli
pullout.
</P>
<P>
Last April, the former Israeli government led by Benjamin
Netanyahu endorsed the 20-year resolution, but conditioned the
withdrawal on a Lebanese government's security guarantee against
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and its ally Syria rejected the offer, asking Israel to
implement the resolution without any conditions.
</P>
<P>
Geremek expressed the hope that Arabs and Israeli politicians
shift their eyes from the past to the future, where he believes
there are opportunities for the resumption of the stalled peace
talks.
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, the Polish foreign minister, who arrived
here Monday morning on a two-day visit, also held talks with
Lebanese President Emile Lahoud and House Speaker Nabih Berri.
</P>
<P>
Following meeting with Hoss, Geremek and Lebanese Finance
Minister George Korom signed an agreement to avoid double
taxation between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
