<HEADLINE> Ghana Appoints New Envoy to Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian President Jerry Rawlings
Monday presented letters of credence to Lieutenant Colonel
Ebenezer Anku-Tsede as High Commissioner-designate to Sierra
Leone, the Ghana News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the peace accord signed in Togolese capital Lome
last month by the Sierra Leonean government and the Revolutionary
United Front (RUF), Rawlings said: "If the accord is going to
improve the situation in Sierra Leone, let us see it."
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the rebels were given four cabinet and four
deputy ministerial posts. And their leader Foday Sankoh has the
rank of vice- president and chairs a commission, which controls
Sierra Leone's mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
During the war, the rebels were reputed to have carried out
brutalities that included amputations, burning, summary
executions, thus drawing condemnation from the international
community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
