<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Fatherland Front President Passes Away </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Le Quang Dao, president of the
Presidium of the Vietnam Fatherland Front (VNFF) Central
Committee, died in Hanoi on July 24, 1999 of illness at the age of
78.
</P>
<P>
This was announced on Monday in a special communique by the
Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) Central Committee, the National
Assembly, the president and the Government of Vietnam and the VNFF
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The special communique says that "Le Quang Dao has made
numerous great contributions to the party and the nation's
revolution" during more than 60 years of participation in
revolutionary activities.
</P>
<P>
"Dao's demise is a great loss to the Communist Party, the state
and people of Vietnam," it says.
</P>
<P>
The CPV Central Committee, the National Assembly, the president
and the government and the VNFF Central Committee declared Tuesday
and Wednesday as state mourning days during which national flags
will be flown at half-mast and all entertainment, cultural and
sports activities will be suspended throughout the country.
Memorial and funeral services will be held in Hanoi on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Le Quang Dao was born on August 8, 1921 in Vietnam's northern
province of Bac Ninh. He joined the revolution at the age of 17,
taking part in the democratic youth and the Indochinese
anti-imperialist youth movements. He was admitted into the
Indochinese Communist Party, now the CPV, in 1940.
</P>
<P>
Le Quang Dao had been secretary of the CPV Central Committee,
chairman of Vietnam's National Assembly and vice president of the
State Council of Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
