<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK to Lose EU influence outside Euro: de Silguy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain risks losing influence in
the European Union because of its reluctance to join the euro, the
outgoing European Monetary Affairs Commissioner Yves-Thibault de
Silguy told a news conference in London on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The euro is changing the dynamics of Europe...and can create
risks to UK influence as the euro has political consequences,"
Reuters quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
The price for the UK of staying outside the euro would increase
with time, and the pound was becoming "a satellite to a much
larger euro," he said.
</P>
<P>
There was a risk of a two-speed Europe, with those countries in
the euro gaining momentum, with a strengthening in particular of a
Franco-German axis, according to De Silguy.
</P>
<P>
He said the UK risked losing influence in key European
institutions, which are designing the framework for the single
currency's operation.
</P>
<P>
Britain has decided to "wait and see" how the euro evolves
before making a decision whether to join or not, though Britain's
ruling Labor party is sympathetic in principle to a common
European currency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
