<HEADLINE> Congo (K) Govt. Claims 3,000 Rebels Surrendered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"They came to their senses after the signing of the cease-fire
agreement" in Zambian capital on July 10 by the heads of state of
the six nations fighting in the DRC, presidential spokesman
Lambert Kaboye said in a statement. He called on the rebels to
lay down their weapons and join the government army.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 rebels of the Congolese Rally for Democracy
(RCD) surrendered last week, John Numbi, the commander of the
