African President Thabo Mbeki Monday, seeking help to solve the
crisis in Congo (K).
</P>
<P>
Mbeki played a prominent role in talks that led to the
cease-fire agreement in the DRC, where rebels allegedly backed by
Uganda and Rwanda have been fighting for nearly a year to oust
Kabila. 
