<HEADLINE> 300 Vehicles Impounded by Dar Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Police in Tanzanian capital
Dar es Salaam have impounded over 300 vehicles and fined the
drivers with a total of 2.1 million shillings (about 2,600 U.S.
dollars) in a special operation.
</P>
<P>
Regional Police Commander Alfred Gewe said here Monday that
these drivers are punished because they have violated traffic
rules or refused to transport students, or operated under
influence of alcohol.
</P>
<P>
The operation was carried out during the middle of this month
and last Thursday, Gewe said, adding that during the period 29
road accidents occurred in the city.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are among the leading causes of deaths in
Tanzania. During 1996-1998, 5,090 people were killed and more
than 37,000 others were injured in more than 42,000 road
accidents.
</P>
<P>
In Dar es Salaam, more than 2,600 road accidents were recorded
in the first eight months of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
