<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Students Win 2 Gold Medals in International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese middle-school students
won two gold medals in the 30th International Physical Olympic
(IPHO) which ended Monday in the Italian north city of Padova.
</P>
<P>
After passing the exams of the theoretical and experimental
physics, which began July 19 in the University of Padova, Ji Tao
from China's Beijing and Jiang Liang from China's southeast
province of Jiang Su, won two of 30 gold medals, another 3 Chinese
students won 3 silver medals.
</P>
<P>
About 300 students from 60 countries took part in the yearly
world-wide physical competition, Russia's Zravtsov Konstantin won
the golden medal with 49.8 points in the exams (full marks are 50
points), being in the lead among all the participants, and Iranian
team, with 5 gold medals in hands, leads other countries.
The next year's IPHO will be held in Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
