<HEADLINE> Russia to Strengthen Air Force Strike Component </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia plans to strengthen its air
force strike component by 10-20 percent in five years, the
Interfax news agency reported, quoting Defense Ministry sources.
</P>
<P>
Russia's strike potential will be raised through an increase
in the size of strategic bombers and attack aviation and the
modernization of existing aircraft.
</P>
<P>
They admitted that the latest developments in the Balkans were
one of the reasons for increasing the strike potential of the air
force.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 MiG-29 jets of the fighter fleet will be updated by
the end of the year. Sukhoi-27 and MiG-31 fighters will also be
involved in the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
New TU-160 strategic bombers will join the existing fleet of
TU-95MC and TU-22MZ aircraft. By 2005 strategic aviation should
take up cruise missiles of a new generation, the ministry sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The existing fleet of front-line aviation should be modernized
and equipped with multi-purpose systems.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that after 2005 the Air Force will start
using multi-purpose aircraft of the fifth generation, Interfax
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
