The German team was second after the first leg as Romania's
Camelia Potec touched ahead of world record-holder Franziska van
Almsick. But Szalai put Germany firmly in front on the second and
the Germans pulled away in the second half of the race to win the
title.
</P>
<P>
Sweden edged Romania for the silver medal by just 0.38 of a
second, touching in 8:07.37.
</P>
<P>
Germany also won the women's 4x100 freestyle event on Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
