<HEADLINE> Australian Financial Institutions Ready for Y2K </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Most Australian financial
institutions' computer systems were now immune from the millennium
or Y2K bug, federal Treasurer Peter Costello said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Year 2000 preparedness of the Australian banking and financial
sector is well advanced with preparations internationally
recognized as being at world's best practice," he said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
