<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Autos, Parts Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports of automobiles,
motorcycles and parts increased by over 40 percent in the first
half of this year, the Federation of Thai Industries (FTI) said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Overall exports of locally-made automobiles, motorcycles,
engines and parts reached 26.7 billion baht (722 million U.S.
dollars), an increase of 40.7 percent from the same period last
year, said Surapong Paisithpatanapong, spokesman for the FTI's
vehicle industry group.
</P>
<P>
Exports of automobiles doubled those of the same period last
year to 53,084 units, worth 20.4 billion baht (552.2 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Thailand also exported auto-engines worth 1.16 billion baht
(31.4 million dollars), an increase of 143.9 percent from the same
period in 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, exports of locally-made motorcycles saw a sharp
decline of 83.8 percent to 17,337 units.
</P>
<P>
Surapong didn't specify the reason for the drop of motorcycle
exports.
</P>
<P>
During the first six months of this year, Thailand produced
133,288 units of automobiles, an increase of 110 percent from the
same period last year, while production of motorcycles rose 8.2
percent to 352,089 units, Surapong said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
