<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Backpedals, Losing Half U.S. Cent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
backpedalled Tuesday, losing more than half a U.S. cent as market
participants abandoned long positions amid concerns for the
Australian currency.
</P>
<P>
The Australian currency finished the day at 64.63 U.S. cents
from 65.15 at Monday's close, after spending the day wedged
between 64.68 and 64.50.
</P>
<P>
In the money market, the 90-day bank bill rate was at 4.89
percent from 4.90 at Monday's close, and the 180-day bill at 5.00
percent from 5.04.
</P>
<P>
Also at the local close, the Australian dollar was buying
0.6034 euro from 0.6190 on Monday, and 75.34 Japanese yen from
75.91. 
</P>
