<HEADLINE> Philippines Records 1,275 Sexual Abuse Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Department of Social Welfare
and Development (DSWD) of the Philippines said Tuesday in a report
that it has received 1,275 sexual abuse cases during the first six
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Most of these cases were brought to the DSWD's Quick Response
Team because they required residential services, said the report.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the DSWD handled 2,746 reported cases of sexual abuse
while the Philippine National Police (PNP) recorded 3,081 cases.
</P>
<P>
The DSWD said the cases were handled through the two different
channels according to their requirements, adding that those
brought to the attention of the DSWD often required protective
custody and residential services, while the PNP received all kinds
of reports.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 report of the DSWD showed that the majority of the
victims of sexual abuse were in the age range of 11 to 15 which
comprised 48 percent of the total number of reported cases.
</P>
<P>
This is also supported by the findings of the Baseline Survey
on Sexual Abuse and Exploitation in the Philippines conducted by
the DSWD and the Community and Family Service International in
December 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
