<HEADLINE> Citybank Joins in Shanghai's ATM/POS Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Citybank today became a member of
Shanghai's ATM/POS Network, which means that anyone with a
Citybank charge card will be able to withdraw Chinese yuan at any
automatic teller machine or point-of-sale location in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Citybank was the first to set up as branch in Shanghai's Pudong
New Area, and also the first to be allowed to do business with the
yuan, both in the zone and in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
John Beeman, governor in charge of Citybank's business in China,
said the bank will intensify cooperation with Chinese enterprises
in electronic-business activities.
</P>
<P>
The ATM/POS network with a total investment of 30 million yuan
(3.6 million U.S.dollars), is now the largest of its kind in China,
with 15 Chinese-funded bank members, 2,200 ATMs, nearly 10,000 POS,
and some ten million bank cards already issued.
</P>
<P>
The review for the first half of this year shows that the
network's trade volume has been 4.14 billion yuan for the ATMs,
and 340 million yuan for the POS. Xin Dingkang, general manager of
the Shanghai Bank Card Network Service Center said that Shanghai's
electronic business will come into full play by the beginning of
the 21st Century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
