<HEADLINE> Performance to Mark Macao's Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- As many as 11,000 people from
various social sectors in Macao will participate in a large-scale
performance on December 21 this year to mark Macao's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 social organizations and schools will take part in
the performance, organizers said at a press conference here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The performance will begin with the thunder of drums and a
spirited lion dance. And the following chorus, shadowboxing and
martial art shows will each be presented by more than 1,000 people.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 singers, dancers and drummers from China's
mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan will join in the performance.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the performance, performers will form the design
of China's national flag and the regional flag of the Macao
Special Administrative Region; two gigantic dragons will roll
around; 1,999 pigeons will fly to the sky; and tens of thousands
of performers and spectators will sing a song to laud the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said the participating social organizations and
schools are busy arranging separate practices since April, and
different groups of performers will join together between
September and November. Two dress rehearsals will be conducted in
mid-December.  
</P>
</TEXT>
