<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily On Struggle Between Materialism &AMP; Idealism (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As China is now in a period of reform and opening-up, the
article says, it has become all the more important for its people
to cherish ideals and pursuits which will foster a pioneering
spirit and the virtues of frugality and perseverance, and hard
work and constant self-improvement.
</P>
<P>
"Marxism does not deny self-cultivation, but it also holds that
such cultivation must be scientific and conform to the spirit of
the times," says the article. "Belief in superstitious ideas and
enthusiasm for dark witcheries and the abandonment of all pursuits
in life and careers do not constitute healthy self-cultivation,
but only leads to the degeneration of humanity."
</P>
<P>
The article continues to say that another intense point of
confrontation between materialism and idealism lies in the
conflict between science and superstition.
</P>
<P>
"Science is a direct result of the materialistic world outlook,
" says the article, adding that science and technology constitute
the number one productive forces, and also provide the
revolutionary power which promotes the advancement of the mankind.
</P>
<P>
"Only by respecting and believing in science and by applying
science to the resolution of realistic problems can society
achieve progress and mankind see hope," it stresses.
</P>
<P>
Though science itself constantly encounters puzzles,
difficulties and even "crises" which challenge its fundamental
theories and research methods, no one can deny the accomplishments
of science, which will continue to develop, the article says.
</P>
<P>
"A real materialist is always full of confidence in science and
in mankind's capacity to recognize and reform the objective world,
" it adds.
</P>
<P>
The article concludes by saying that with materialism and
modern science gradually assuming a prevailing role in the world
today, any idealistic ideas attempting to earn popularity will
have to put on the cloak of superstition and witchery and deceive
the people by various vulgar means, just as Falun Gong did.
</P>
<P>
"Dialectic and historical materialism is a powerful ideological
weapon which will help us triumph over all mistakes and
superstitious ideas," the article says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
