<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Water Levels Lower in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Water levels at the Jiujiang
section of the Yangtze River and at Poyang Lake in east China's
Jiangxi Province has been dropping in the last two days.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial flood-control headquarters said
that the water level at Jiujiang was 22.22 meters at 2:00 p.m.
Monday, 0.11 meter lower than the day before.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the water levels at the Hukou and
Xingzi sections of Poyang Lake were 21.66 meters and 21.63 meters
at 2:00 p.m. today, 0.10 meter and 0.09 meter lower than the
previous day, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Although water levels are now falling, they still exceed the
danger line, and have remained there for 27 days.
</P>
<P>
Soaked with high flood waters, the river dykes have been found
to have 1,725 danger spots over the past month, the official said,
but no severe damage has been reported.
</P>
<P>
Predictions say there will be showers and strong winds tonight
to tomorrow morning across most parts of the province.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters has called for greater flood-control efforts
during the coming period of heavy rain. At present, about 350,000
civilians and soldiers are involved in flood-fighting efforts
along the dykes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Set Up Foreign Investment Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government Tuesday
decided to set up a foreign investment implementation authority
(FIIA) to provide single-window clearance for projects abroad.
</P>
<P>
Information Minister Pramod Mahajah said the authority will
provide "pro-active, one-stop after-care service" to foreign
investors in obtaining necessary approvals, sorting out
operational and coordination problems with different departments
of the government.
</P>
<P>
The authority will set up a fast track committee to review and
monitor mega projects and initiate inter-ministerial consultations
to resolve policy problems.
</P>
<P>
In the past eight years, the actual inflow of foreign direct
investment in the country was only 16.62 billion U.S. dollars as
against the total approval of 55.63 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
