<HEADLINE> 11 People Killed in Bus bomb Explosion in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 11 people were killed
and 30 others injured Tuesday when a bomb ripped through a
passenger bus near Kotli, about 150 kilometers southeast of
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The bus was proceeding from Rawalpindi, Islamabad's sister
city, to Kotli located in Pakistan-administered Kashmir when the
bomb went off in Hajiabad, five kilometers away from Kotli town,
sources from the area told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The bus was totally damaged as the result of the bomb blast. So
far, at least 11 people have been killed, and among the injured
who have been rushed to nearby hospitals, some are in very serious
condition, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Sabir Hussain, senior police superintendent in Kotli, blamed
the Indian intelligence agency, RAW, for the bomb blast, and
described it as a terrorist act.
</P>
<P>
India wanted to create unrest and instability in Pakistan-
administered Kashmir, Hussain said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
