<HEADLINE> Chinese, U.S. Officials Discuss Trade (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has all
along attached great importance to the improvement and development
of Sino-U.S. relations, a senior Chinese trade official said today.
</P>
<P>
Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation (MOFTEC), told U.S. Deputy Secretary of Commerce David
Aaron, who is here for a two-day visit, that keeping sound and
stable ties between the two countries accords with the common
interests of both, and is conducive to world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
However, barriers affecting the further development of Sino-U.S.
ties, including in the economic and trade sectors, still exist,
Sun said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that the United States properly handles the
incident of the U.S.-led NATO's attack on Chinese embassy in
Belgrade, and take concrete actions to make an explanation
satisfactory to the Chinese people and government, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister also said that the Cox report is based on
sheer fabrication, and has enormously poisoned the atmosphere for
economic and technological exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The Cox report has seriously reduced U.S. technology export to
China, he pointed out.
</P>
</TEXT>
