<HEADLINE> Youth Urged to Uphold Science and Oppose Superstition (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A Special Commentator's article
released by the Xinhua News Agency today calls on the youth of
China to become an effective force for upholding science and
opposing superstition.
</P>
<P>
"With the Party Central Committee's decision to ban Falun Gong,
and the revocation of the Research Society of Falun Dafa and its
subordinate organizations, the Chinese people have come to
recognize the true face of Falun Gong," the article says.
</P>
<P>
Founded by Li Hongzhi, the Falun Gong organization was banned
by Chinese authorities last Thursday as an "illegal organization"
spreading superstition and fallacies and disrupting social order
in the name of physical fitness exercises.
</P>
<P>
Although a very small number of the Falun Gong practitioners
are young people, members of the Communist Youth League of China
in particular, we should not underestimate the harm and influence
that Falun Gong could do to the young, according to the article.
</P>
<P>
"Arming the youth with scientific theory and calling on them to
advocate science and eradicate superstition is a matter of
importance that concerns the future and destiny of the Party and
the country, and will always remain an important task for us," the
article continues. "Young people should become an effective force
for advocating science and opposing superstition, and firmly fight
against Falun Dafa, founded by Li Hongzhi."
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the glorious tradition of Chinese youth's advocacy of
science, the article mentions the May 4 Movement of 80 years ago,
when young Chinese held high the banner of patriotism, progress,
democracy, and science, and spread Marxism in China to enlighten
the broad masses.
</P>
<P>
After a half-century of struggle under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China, the Chinese people finally founded the
People's Republic of China and embarked on the path toward
prosperity, democracy, and civilization, the article says, adding
that Chinese are becoming increasingly aware of the role of
science in social life and the progress of mankind.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Youth Urged to Uphold Science and Oppose Superstition (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Only by depending on science can we promote national
development and get an upper hand in the international arena in
the future," the article says. "To meet the challenge of
international competition, we have mapped out a strategy for
invigorating the country through science and education."
</P>
<P>
The article also calls for modern young Chinese to inherit and
carry forward the glorious tradition of the May 4 Movement, study
hard, and acquire scientific knowledge to achieve success.
</P>
<P>
Referring to science and superstition as two opposite forces,
the articles says attitudes toward these two forces impact social
development in differing manners. "Young people should master
modern scientific knowledge and firmly fight against superstition
to become an active force for promoting social progress and
carrying out the historical mission of revitalizing the Chinese
nation."
</P>
<P>
"Marxism provides a scientific world outlook which is already
proven by history, and is a strong weapon enabling us to
understand and reform the world," the article says. "Only when we
firmly believe in Marxism, can we advocate science and oppose
superstition effectively."
</P>
<P>
The article goes on to say that the fight against the fallacies
of Li Hongzhi will help youth to distinguish science from pseudo-
science and materialism from idealism, and realize the difference
between a healthy and civilized lifestyle and a fatuous and
unhealthy lifestyle, and thereby become an effective force for
advocating science and eradicating superstition.
</P>
<P>
Calling on youth to arm themselves with scientific theory and
knowledge and a scientific world outlook and staunch faith, the
articles concludes by saying that the growth of a new generation
is the hope of the socialist cause and the hope of the Chinese
people as they aim to achieve prosperity in the 21st century.
</P>
