<HEADLINE> People's Daily On Struggle Between Materialism &AMP; Idealism (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, today published a signed article highlighting
the confrontation between materialism and idealism and warning the
Chinese people against any individuals or groups spreading
idealism through vulgar means.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, an organization named Falun Gong has, in the
name of science and physical fitness exercises, fanatically spread
idealistic concepts by some extremely vulgar means," says the
article, written by Yue Yan and titled Watch Out And Recognize
Idealism In Vulgar Forms -- An Analysis Of the Nature Of Falun
Dafa.
</P>
<P>
The Falun Gong (or Falun Dafa) organization was banned last
Thursday by Chinese authorities as an illegal organization
spreading superstitious and heretical ideas and disrupting social
stability.
</P>
<P>
"The Falun Gong issue has sparked a struggle between atheism
and theism, superstition and science, and idealism and materialism
in China," says the article.
</P>
<P>
It has also highlighted the importance and urgency of carrying
out education on dialectic and historical materialism and
promulgating modern scientific and cultural knowledge among all
members of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the entire
Chinese people, the article adds.
</P>
<P>
"Idealism advocates theism and attributes the development of
the objective world to supernatural forces, thus creating gods,"
explains the article, adding that the so-called "God's will" is in
fact the will of man. It points to the fact that leaders of many
superstitious and cultist organizations, in order to attain
certain specific political and social objectives, often disguise
themselves as "prophets" or even "gods" to deceive the public.
</P>
<P>
"Li Hongzhi, founder and head of Falun Gong, is just one such
person," says the article.
</P>
<P>
According to the article, all Marxists are atheists and their
ideals and beliefs lie in the realization of socialism and
communism, which is a scientific belief established on a realistic
foundation.
</P>
<P>
"The great achievements the Chinese people have scored in
building socialism with Chinese characteristics have proved the
realistic nature of socialism, as well as the fact that socialism
and communism are a scientific ideal which can be realized some
day," it notes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
