<HEADLINE> Irvine Still Tips Hakkinen as Title Favorite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Eddie Irvine won the Austrian Grand
Prix to throw open the Formula One world championship but he still
believed Mika Hakkinen is the favorite to retain his title.
</P>
<P>
Irvine's win at Austrian Grand Prix boosted Ferrari's hopes of
winning both the driver's and constructor's titles this season
since its number one driver Michael Schumacher broke his leg two
weeks ago at Silverstone.
</P>
<P>
Irvine's win at Zeltweg, his second this season, promoted him
within two points of Hakkinen.
</P>
<P>
"The championship is certainly much more interesting now.
Hakkinen is the number-one threat in the points table and I'm
going to make a fight of it." said Irvine.
</P>
<P>
But Irvine admitted: "Mika is still the favourite. He's faster
at the moment, although Ferrari are working hard on improvements."
</P>
