<HEADLINE> 7 Tamil Smugglers Arrested in South India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Indian police arrested Sunday
seven Sri Lankan Tamils who attempted to smuggle medicinal items
in south India, media sources here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the arrested were suspected of carrying drugs
for the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in Wanni in north
Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
All-India Radio Tuesday morning reported that the suspects were
later produced before the Madurai Magistrate and remanded, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Tamil Nadu police and Indian coast guards have recently
intensified surveillance along the southern coast following
reports that the LTTE was extensively engaged in smuggling
activities.
</P>
<P>
Recently a team of high-ranking Sri Lankan naval officials met
with defense officials in New Delhi and had elaborate discussions
on the LTTE's smuggling activities across the Palk Strait.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's navy also has intensified its surveillance along
the northwestern coast of Sri Lanka, which is actively used by
the LTTE for smuggling arms, ammunition and medicinal items, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a war against the Sri Lankan
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the island country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
