<HEADLINE> Fiscal Prudence Important for Hong Kong: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) government said Tuesday that
fiscal prudence is important for Hong Kong's success.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the remarks in response to media reports on
the views on the budgetary strategy and the revenue and
expenditure proposals, including the call for the drawing up of
deficit budgets for 2000/01 and the years to come.
</P>
<P>
"The government fully understands the community's expectations
for more economic relief measures. However, it is important to
bear in mind that under the Basic Law, the SAR government must
maintain a fiscal balance, avoid deficits and keep the growth of
government expenditure commensurate with the growth rate of its
gross domestic product," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Prudent financial management is an important pillar of the
fiscal policy which Hong Kong has successfully followed for years.
It is vital to our economic well-being that we maintain that
fiscal prudence so as to retain the confidence of the
international financial community and overseas investors," he said.
</P>
<P>
Events in the aftermath of the Asian financial crisis and their
impact on public finances have highlighted the importance, in
drawing up budget proposals, to give due regard to the prevailing
economic circumstances as well as the economic prospects in the
medium terms, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
