<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index added
20.02 points to 796.20, the all-share Emas index was up 7.43
points to 207.75, the Industrial Index surged 48.05 points to
1,395.9 and the Second Board index gained 8.03 points to 177.5.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 716 to 61 while 54 counters were
unchanged, 86 counters untraded and 13 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 860.481 million shares valued
at 1.814 billion ringgit (477.368 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 858.436 million shares valued at 1.811 billion ringgit
(476.578 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
