<HEADLINE> Teen-Ager Quality Upgrading Program Kicks Off in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A program designed to upgrade the
survival, development and innovation abilities of Chinese teen-
agers has kicked off in the country.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, China will set up quality-upgrading bases in
the country, involving subjects such as national defense, ecology,
labor, survival and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
In addition, training centers of various knowledges will also
be established, according to the program's initiator-the Central
Committee of the Communist Youth League of China (CYLC).
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to help upgrade the moral, cultural,
working and physical qualities of Chinese teen-agers, and promote
the overall development of their bodies and minds.
</P>
<P>
Currently, China boasts 36 activity camps, and about 500
training centers for teen-agers.
</P>
<P>
The CYLC plans to establish 100 training bases, 1,000 training
centers and a physique building and testing network in the country.
</P>
<P>
By then, about 10 million Chinese teen-agers will be able to
participate in various training activities, according to the
league. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
