<HEADLINE> Works of Chilean Photographer Exhibited in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua)-- A total of 39 works by Chilean
woman photographer Paz Errazuriz was put on show at the Royal
Exhibition Hall of Beijing as of today.
</P>
<P>
The two-week long exhibition, sponsored by the Chinese Ministry
of Culture, is an important part of the newly signed cultural
cooperation agreement for 1999 to 2001 between the Chinese and
Chilean governments.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition includes a collection of landscapes and
portraits of the remaining men and women of three peoples of the
extreme south of Chile that are on the very verge of extinction:
ona, yagan, and alacaluf, skilled people of the sea, and the very
first inhabitants of the southernmost territories of the American
continent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
