<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Computer Giant to Be Listed in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's computer giant Great Wall
Technology Co., Ltd. will be listed in Hong Kong on August 5,
Xinhua learned today.
</P>
<P>
According to information faxed to Xinhua by the Shenzhen-based
company, Great Wall is placing 355 million new shares at an issue
price of 3.15 Hong Kong dollars per share.
</P>
<P>
Ten percent of the share offer is for public subscription in
Hong Kong from July 26 to 30, while the remaining 90 percent is
allocated to international placing.
</P>
<P>
The company said its global recommendation campaign from July
14 to July 22 has been so successful that even after it raised the
price from the originally-planned 2.22 to 2.78 Hong Kong dollars
to 3.15 dollars, subscriptions by international investors hit
eight times over the total issue.
</P>
<P>
The company expects to raise over 184.4 million U.S. dollars
from the issue.
</P>
<P>
It plans to use the proceeds to fund the expansion of
production facilities and office buildings in connection with the
establishment of production facilities for hard disk drives for
personal computers and to invest in a joint venture project with
the U.S.-based Texas Instruments.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to invest in Internet and mobile phone
development, company officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
