<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sends 338,000 Laborers Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China has sent more laborers to
work abroad these years and its overseas work force had grown to
338,000 by the end of June this year, according to the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
The figure represented an increase of 14,000 people over the
end of June last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, China made great progress in
signing contracts with developed countries in Europe and North
America while going on smoothly with large projects signed with
African countries, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
While the number of projects, especially large projects, kept
growing, the technical level of these projects has been upgraded,
too, according to the MOFTEC.
</P>
<P>
China's labor export and foreign project contracts have been
growing rapidly since 1978, and there remains huge potential in
this market, for China's labor export accounts for only one
percent of the shifting work force in the world.
</P>
<P>
The MOFTEC has pledged to give a boost to the development of
foreign project contracts and labor export by granting more
companies access to the business and exploring the European market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
