<HEADLINE> China's Finance Departments Mobilized for Anti-Flood Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's Finance Ministry has
recently urged local finance departments to give top priority to
the anti-flood work in a bid to fend off damages that might be
caused by the coming summer floods.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has issued a directive requiring all local
branches to raise enough funds to support the reinforcement and
renovation of dams and other anti-flood structures.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also urged local finance departments to strengthen
supervision over the use of funds to ensure timely allocation and
avoid diversion of the funds.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji has called for increased efforts in
flood control along the Yangtze River earlier this month, saying
that the flood-control work is of great significance this year
since China is to celebrate its 50th anniversary and Macao is
expected to return to the embrace of the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
