<HEADLINE> URGENT: Detonator Explosion Kills 13, Wounds 41 in SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A truck carrying detonators
exploded at 9:40 a.m. today in Changshou County, southwest China's
Chongqing Municipality, killing 13 people and injuring 41 others
as of press time.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told Xinhua that a collision of the truck, which
started from neighboring Yunnan Province, and a taxi might cause
the explosion which lasted nearly half an hour and damaged a
building nearby.
</P>
<P>
Investigation of the explosion is under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
