<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Launch Anti-Malaria Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian health
authorities have called on its people to participate in
anti-malaria campaign due to start next month.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Kebede, senior official of the Ministry of Health, told
local press Monday that governmental organizations as well as the
public should join hands to contain the spread of malaria, a
common disease in the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
An anti-malaria week has been observed for years in Ethiopia
nationwide from August 24 to 30 when programs to raise public
awareness on malaria control mechanisms are conducted.
</P>
<P>
August is a month suitable for malaria breeding in most parts
of the country, according local medical experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
