<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Celebrate 2,550th Birth Anniversary Of Confucius </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China plans to hold a "Confucius
Culture Week" in Beijing on September 6-12 to celebrate the 2,
550th birth anniversary of the scholar Confucius.
</P>
<P>
The event is being organized by the Beijing Administration of
Cultural Heritage and the Beijing Tourism Administration. There
will be an exhibition on Confucius and Confucianism, a seminar on
his philosophy, and traditional songs and dances, according to the
organizing committee. Beijing TV Guide Weekly also carried a quiz
on Monday on Confucius-related subjects,
</P>
<P>
Foreigners are being asked to take part in a writing
competition on "Visiting the Temple of Confucius in Beijing" and "
Confucius in My Heart", the results of which will be published in
China Daily, the country's major English language newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Confucius (551 B.C.-479 B.C.) is regarded as a great thinker
and educator in ancient China. Confucianism, which had dominated
China's political, cultural and social life for thousands of years,
was based upon his teachings and was studied by scholars in China
and other Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
His birthday was set as October 9 recently by Chinese scholars
using computerized data. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
