<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Island Province Getting More Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's Hainan Province had 200,000
overseas tourists in the first half of this year, up 4.6 percent
from the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Revenues from overseas tourists amounted to 50 million U.S.
dollars for the period, according to Chen Chuanmin, director of
the provincial tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
The province is expected to be a premier spot for overseas
tourists and has built 13 four-star hotels and opened seven
international charter flight routes, he said.
</P>
<P>
To attract more tourists, the province allows tourists to get a
visa when they arrive at the local airport.
</P>
<P>
The province's tourism department has also built a number of
jointly-funded hotels and travel services with overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The province will hold a worldwide tourism promotion drive with
the theme "Hainan Island -- Tropics in China" later this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
