<HEADLINE> Van With Disposable Lighters Explodes in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A container van with disposable
lighters exploded and caught fire in Jose Abad Santos avenue in
Metro Manila shortly after 13:00 Tuesday, a police report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the explosion hurled hundreds of
disposable lighters from the van and the lighters landed in
different directions on the avenue's stretch.
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the explosion and the fire on the van was
quickly put off by responding firemen, the report said.
</P>
<P>
To stop people in the neighborhood from scrambling for the
loot, police have cordoned off the place.
</P>
<P>
Police have mounted an investigation of the incident while the
van's driver and helpers are still at large, said the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
