<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
closed lower here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was 17 points lower at 2,163 with a light
turnover of 70 million NZ dollars (37 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Most leading stocks went down with Telstra falling 35 cents to
1,030 cents, and Fletcher Energy 28 cents to 532 cents.
</P>
<P>
Contact Energy shed 7 cents to 296 cents, Telecom 6 to 811
cents, Fletcher Building 5 to 280 cents, Sky Network and Fletcher
Paper 4 each to 360 and 150 cents respectively, Carter Holt
Harvey 2 to 238 cents, and Fletcher Forests 1 cent to 106 cents.
</P>
<P>
Corporate Investments went against the general trend, edging up
1 cent to 85 cents. 
</P>
