<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand to Lease U.S. Fighter Jets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand government has
approved leasing 28 F-16 fighter jets from the United States for
ten years, the Dominion Tuesday quoted the NZ defense minister as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Max Bradford said the Cabinet has approved the deal along with
buying a third navy helicopter. It has also approved in principle
buying 423 light operational vehicles to replace the army's
Land-Rovers.
</P>
<P>
The Wellington-based newspaper also quoted the minister as
saying the two five-year leases for the 28 fighters will cost
124.8 million NZ dollars (66.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"There is an option to buy the aircraft for 287 million NZ
dollars (153 million U.S. dollars) after ten years," he said.
</P>
<P>
The lease is likely to be signed in the United States later
this month, Bradford said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
