<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Petrol Price Rises by Another 3 cents in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Shell is increasing petrol
prices by another three cents of the New Zealand dollar a liter,
the second rise in a fortnight in New Zealand, and more increases
are not ruled out.
</P>
<P>
The Evening Post Tuesday quoted Shell as announcing it is
lifting wholesale petrol and diesel prices by three cents a liter
from Tuesday midnight.
</P>
<P>
Mobil, Caltex and BP (British Petroleum) are considering
whether to raise their prices in New Zealand, the Wellington-based
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Shell blames sharply higher international crude oil prices for
the latest increase.
</P>
<P>
Its spokesman said the three cent rise imposed by all petrol
companies in New Zealand two weeks ago is insufficient to recoup
the increased costs of crude oil.
</P>
<P>
The six cent petrol price rise still leaves room for another
three or four cent increase, "but we're in a competitive market
and we want to remain competitive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The latest petrol price rise will take the price of Shell 91
octane to 86 cents of the NZ dollar (46 cents of the U.S. dollar)
a liter in the main centers in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
