<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Laos to Resolve Border Issue With Cambodia by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Lao government said Tuesday
that it will resolve the border issue with Cambodia by the end of
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Laos Ambassador to Cambodia Ly
Southavilay in a press conference here, and it is the first time
the Lao government made such a statement on border issue.
</P>
<P>
Ly Southavilay said, "The Lao People's Democratic Republic is
willing to resolve the border issue by the end of the year 2000."
</P>
<P>
"Laos has no intention to violate Cambodian territory as some
local media had reported," he added.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia has border issues with Vietnam, Thailand and Laos. In
recent months, the border issues have aroused growing attention
among the Cambodian media and students who have held several
pretests over the territorial issues.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia and Vietnam have already agreed to finalize all
outstanding border problems before the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia and Laos share a common border of about 535
kilometers, while Cambodia and Vietnam's common border stretches
for 1,130 Kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
