<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Working More At Preserving Ethnic Minority Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has made
great efforts to preserve documents of its ethnic groups over the
past four decades.
</P>
<P>
The China National Minorities Library has 400,000 documents
that cover a long period of time, according to a meeting marking
the 20th anniversary of the China Society of Library Science,
which has just ended in Dalian in Liaoning Province. They include
170,000 books in Mongolian, Tibetan, Uygur, Zhuang, and 20 other
ethnic languages.
</P>
<P>
Chinese publishers have printed more than 1,000 titles of
ancient texts from ethnic groups and there are over 600 ethnic
minority libraries in China, containing 30 million books in all.
</P>
<P>
Libraries in the Inner Mongolia, Guangxi Zhuang, Tibet, Ningxia
Hui, and Xinjiang Uygur autonomous regions have 5.18 million books.
</P>
</TEXT>
