<HEADLINE> Indian Fertilizer Output Rises 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- India's fertilizer production
went up by 9.6 percent to 3.235 million tons during the first
quarter of the current fiscal year against 2.952 million tons a
year ago, according to the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
During the quarter ending in June, estimated production of
nitrogenous fertilizers was 8.2 percent higher at 2.496 million
tons compared with 2.306 million tons in April-June 1998.
</P>
<P>
Production of phosphatic fertilizers went up by 14.4 percent to
739,000 tons from 646,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The estimated production of fertilizers in June was 920,000
tons of nitrogen and 259,000 tons of phosphate against the target
of 901,000 tons and 266,000 tons. 
</P>
