<HEADLINE> China to Send 145 Athletes to Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China will send 145 People's
Liberation Army (PLA) athletes to compete in 15 of the 24 sports
at the Military World Games in Zagreb, Croatia, next month, Chef
de Mission Major General Chen Youyuan said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chen was speaking at a ceremony inaugurating China's team for
the August 8-17 games. General Fu Quanyou, Chief of the General
Staff of the PLA, attended.
</P>
<P>
China will compete in military pentathlon, shooting,
parachuting, judo, wrestling, taekwondo, boxing, fencing, track
and field, triathlon, cycling, swimming, diving, volleyball and
lifesaving.
</P>
<P>
Stars in the delegation include Asian Games women's 50 meters
and 100 meters swimming champion Shan Ying and Atlanta Olympics
women's sports pistol gold medalist Li Duihong.
</P>
<P>
General Fu said the games would be a good chance to showcase
the achievements of the construction of the PLA in a year when the
People's Republic of China is to celebrate its 50th anniversary of
founding in October and Macao's return to the motherland in
December.
</P>
<P>
Major General Chen said: "We have more world-class athletes in
the delegation and would like to win more medals than we had in
the last Military World Games in Rome four years ago."
</P>
<P>
In Rome, China won 13 golds, 21 silvers and 15 bronzes at the
inaugural edition of the games. 
