<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Greek Ships Collide in Aegean Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Greek ships collided in
northern Aegean Sea along the Turkish coast early Tuesday morning
and the two crew members on board are missing, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a 3,982-ton Greek cargo ship named "Pel
Mariner" sank after colliding with another ship named "Pel
Ranger" in the open sea of the Aegean.
</P>
<P>
Ten other seamen were rescued after the incident, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the two ships had collided with each other
due to dense fog. 
</P>
</TEXT>
