<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Pakistani Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Pakistani English newspapers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The News:
</P>
<P>
-- Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz has expressed the hope that
India would respect the Line of Control (LoC) by vacating areas,
which do not belong to it, saying the LoC is a temporary line and
Pakistan has never accepted Kashmir as part of India.
</P>
<P>
The Nation:
</P>
<P>
-- The leader of the Opposition and chairperson of Pakistan
People's Party, Benazir Bhutto, accused Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif on Monday of destroying the country's economy and called
for an All-Party National Assembly investigation as to how the
previous IMF funds were utilized.
</P>
<P>
The Frontier Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Pakistan's Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Siddique
Khan Kanju said Monday that the focus has shifted from "peripheral
issues to core issue of Kashmir," in the post-Kargil situation
which he called a qualitative change. 
</P>
