<HEADLINE> Bulls Sign Top Overall Pick Elton Brand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Forward Elton Brand, the top
overall pick in last month's draft, flew to Chicago today and
signed a three-year, 8.86 million dollars contract with the Bulls.
</P>
<P>
Brand arrived in Chicago and underwent a physical examination
before signing, according to a team spokeswoman. He is expected to
join the team's entry in the summer league in Salt Lake City.
</P>
<P>
"I'm really excited to be with the Bulls and I'm looking
forward to joining coach Tim Floyd and the rest of the team in
Utah," Brand said. "I realize the expectations that come with
being the overall No. 1 draft pick, and I'm going to work hard to
live up to those expectations."
</P>
<P>
Brand had been in Puerto Rico playing with Team USA, which
secured a berth in the Olympics on Saturday and won the gold medal
Sunday in the Pre-Olympic Qualifying Tournament of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls did not disclose financial terms. However, under the
collective bargaining agreement, Brand will receive 8.861 million
dollars for three years, and the Bulls have a fourth-year option
at 3.868 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Brand became the first player to leave Duke Unviersity early
during the tenure of coach Mike Krazyzewski. He left after a
sophomore season in which he averaged team highs of 17.7 points
and 9.8 rebounds. He led the Blue Devils to a 37-2 mark and the
NCAA Tournament title game, where they were upset by Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
Brand was named Atlantic Coast Conference Player of the Year
and won the Wooden Award as the nationa's best college basketball
player. 
