<HEADLINE> IT Industry Growth On Chinese Island Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Information technology (IT) is now
being used for economic growth and government administration in
south China's Hainan Province to improve efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Hainan is the country's youngest province and biggest special
economic zone, It has more than 200 information technology
companies and has some 20,000 customers. The IT companies did 1.33
billion yuan worth of business in 1998, about a billion yuan more
than in 1993, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
It started putting the whole island online in 1997 and the
provincial government published administrative decrees on the
information network and set forth ideas on developing the IT
industry and supporting IT companies last year. It also announced
preferential treatment in taxes, financing, and imports and
exports for IT companies.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to infrastructure improvements, there are specialized
telecommunications, education, science and technology, economic
information, cable TV, and public security networks and related
systems for tourism booking and tropical agriculture information
on the island. CHINANET and HINET, a public information network
designed for Hainan Province, provide some of the most diverse
services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
