with Damian Ordas and Walter Balunek kicking up in the last 500m
to beat Brazilian pairs Alexandre Soares and Gibran Cunha and
wrapping up the title in 6:40.49. The Brazilians were at 6:40.75
for the silver.
</P>
<P>
In the men's lightweight single scull, American William Belden
won the race in 7:23.51, with Cuban Martin Hernandez second at 7:
26.59.
</P>
<P>
Mexico had a big show-off at the Pan Am 20km walk race as
Bernardo Segura slashed more than two minutes off the Games record
to win the men's event in one hour 20 minutes 17 seconds and his
teammate, the 36-year-old veteran M. Mendoza took the women's
title in 1:34:19.
</P>
<P>
Morgan White of the United States claimed the women's
gymnastics all-round title by skin of the teeth here on Monday,
totalling 37.649 points to hold off heavily-favored Canadian
Michelle Conway by a slender margin of 0.031 points.
</P>
<P>
Matthew Emmons shot down another gold for the United States,
collecting 104.0 points to win the men's free rifle prone title.
</P>
<P>
In the volleyball preliminaries, the United States scored a
scared 20-25, 25-17, 16-25, 25-19, 15-12 win over underdogs
Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Carribean country Netherlands Antilles got off to the medals
table here today, with Anthony Boelbaai winning karate's up to 70
kg event. 
