<HEADLINE> Village Of Twins in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The village of Bazhou in Central
China's Hunan Province is known as the "Village of Twins" because
its women for generations have borne twins.
</P>
<P>
The village with 427 families have 18 pairs of twins and even
when women marry outside the village they have a large chance of
giving birth to twins.
</P>
<P>
Shu Xiaoliang and Shu Xiaoyi, who are 61, are the oldest twins,
and the youngest are 2. Shu Xiaoyi said that villagers often
confuse twin brothers and sisters and there are many jokes about
this at the village school. He said that his mother's sister also
gave birth to twins and his wife's family has had this legacy for
three generations.
</P>
<P>
The chance of having twins is quite low, according to doctors
at Hunan Medical Sciences University, and the director of its
Genetics Lab, Xia Jiahui, said that the phenomenon here is still a
mystery.
</P>
<P>
The environment and medicine can affect the possibility, but
genetic factors are generally considered to have a major effect,
Xia said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
