<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Morgan White of the
United States claimed the Pan Am women's gymnastics all-around
title by skin of the teeth here on Monday, holding off heavily-
favored Canadian Michelle Conway by a slender margin of 0.031
points.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old American botched her vault routines, managing a
modest 9.087 points before putting herself together for a steady
and solid showing later on, which earned her a total of 37.649
points and a gold medal.
</P>
<P>
But the day-high performance was executed by White's closest
rival Conway. The inspiration for Canada's women team triumph on
Saturday churned out a superb 9.750 points for her near-flawless
floor exercise, but still missed out on the title with 37.618
points.
</P>
<P>
White's teammate Jennie Thompson added a bronze to the United
States by accumulating 37.236 points. 
