<HEADLINE> Argentine Business Delegation Visits Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- An Argentine business delegation
arrived here over the weekend to explore possibilities of
establishing joint ventures with Cuban enterprises, press reports
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by Jose Rosas Velazquez, director of
Argentina's International Trade Assembly, is comprised of 30
representatives from medium and large companies.
</P>
<P>
They will focus on cooperation with their Cuban counterparts in
the areas of farming machinery as well as rail and car parts, the
reports said.
