<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, during his visit to Hunan
Province from July 23 to 25, urged people along the Yangtze River
to maintain high vigilance and make careful inspections of the
river embankments to ensure the safety of major cities and people'
s lives.
</P>
<P>
Zhu inspected water-control projects in Changsha, capital of
central China's Hunan Province, on the afternoon of July 23,
visited flood victims in the Ziyang District on July 24 where a
secondary dyke had broken, and toured the Yongji section of the
Yangtze River and the Chenglingji hydrologic station on July 25.
</P>
<P>
The flood situation at some sections of the Yangtze is more
serious than it was last year, as heavier rains are expected in
the region shortly, and a number of embankment reinforcing
projects have to be completed, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
-- A commentary published today points out that Chinese
territory and sovereignty can not be separated.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui openly publicized his "Two-States" statement
through overseas media, exposing his real ambition to split
Chinese territory and sovereignty, the article said.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- A special commentator's article urges all members of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) to fully recognize the political
nature and serious harm of Falun Gong and support the CPC Central
Committee's decision to forbid all Party members to practice Falun
Gong.
</P>
<P>
"The Party Central Committee's decision to ban Falun Gong has
great significance for strengthening Party building, maintaining
the vanguard role and purity of the Party, and safeguarding the
overall situation of reform, development and stability," says the
article.
</P>
<P>
There remain several misconceptions among some CPC members who
were involved in the practice of Falun Dafa, or Falun Gong, and it
is necessary to help these Party members to see the truth, the
article says.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese scientists continue to criticize Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan told the Sixth ASEAN
regional forum that the forum should continue to focus on
confidence-building measures and that China will support ASEAN by
continuing to play a leading role in this aspect.
</P>
<P>
"There is a huge scope for developing and deepening co-
operation in confidence," Tang said. "Efforts in this field should
continue in the future."
</P>
<P>
-- The country's top education authority has outlined a program
to encourage colleges and universities to play a greater role in
economic growth, especially in the high-tech sector. 
</P>
