<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed on Monday with Benchmark IPC index losing 427.61 points, or
3.31 percent, at 5,427.61.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 63.370 million shares for an amount of some
89.743 million U.S. dollars against 105.897 million shares worth
155.743 million dollars on Friday, when the stocks closed last
week's sessions.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.55 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico city, the same as rates on Friday. 
