<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal Wins Euro Under-18 Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Portugal scored a lone goal
against Italy, winning the title of the European under-18 soccer
tournament in Norrkoping, Sweden on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The decisive goal was netted in the 33rd minute by Joao Paulo
as the Portugese eleven resorted to aggressive tactics with a
string of attacks launched in front of the Italian goalmouth.
</P>
<P>
The Italians only intensified their attacks after the break and
especially after Portugal was reduced to ten men in the 64th
minute, but still failed to find the target as the Portugese were
unwilling to give up their hard-fought victory.
</P>
<P>
Italian coach Rosario Rampanti explained that the defeat was
mostly due to mental pressure as the Italians failed to live up to
their competitive level as they were afraid of losing the match.
</P>
<P>
In the third-place playoff in Linkoping, defending champion
Ireland outscored Greece 1-0 for the bronze medal in the eight-
member tournament started on July 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
