<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Snooker Star Clarke Fined for Marijuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Snooker star Scot Darren Clarke has
been fined 2,600 pounds after testing positive for marijuana
during a tournament.
</P>
<P>
Clarke submitted a positive urine sample on the day of his 5-1
defeat to Scotland's Chris Small at the Scottish Open in Aberdeen
in February.
</P>
<P>
He was fined 2,600 pounds by the World Professional Billiards
and Snooker Association, his earnings for reaching the second
round of the event after defeating Steve Davis.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting of the WPBSA's disciplinary committee, Clarke
confirmed the sample contained marijuana, which meant he was in
breach of two rules relating to the presence of banned substances.
</P>
<P>
The disciplinary committee automatically disqualified Clarke
from the tournament, leading to his forfeiture of the 2,600 prize
money and 855 ranking points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
