<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rios Withdraws from LA Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelo Rios withdrew
from the Mercedes-Benz Cup tennis tournament because of injuries
in both hips on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Rios, fourth seed of the tournament, was to play Magnus Larsson
of Sweden on Tuesday. Instead, he was replaced by lucky loser
Paradon Srichaphan of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Rios, the world's 13th-ranked player, was very successful in
the ATP Tour last year, winning seven titles and once became world
No. 1.
</P>
<P>
However, injuries have dragged him back this year, including a
bad back that kept him from playing Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
"It's been the worst year of my career," he said. "It's the
first time I'm so injured in four years." 
</P>
</TEXT>
