<HEADLINE> Clinton Urges Assad to Seize Opportunity for Negotiation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton has
urged Syrian President Hafez Assad to "seize the moment of
opportunity" for peace negotiations with Israel, a U.S. official
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The official said Clinton made the remarks in a letter sent
over the weekend. Clinton told Assad he had confidence Israeli
Prime Minister Ehud Barak was willing to hold peace talks with
Syria after a three-year stalemate.
</P>
<P>
Clinton also told the Syrian leader about the four days of
talks he held in Washington with Barak.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said he hoped Assad to stay in touch with him.
</P>
