<HEADLINE> UNDP Project in Pakistan to Help Conserve Biodiversity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A 10.35 million dollar
UNDP/Global Environment Facility project has been approved to
safeguard biodiversity in Pakistan's high mountain areas, it was
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The program launched this month by the U.N. agencies and the
Pakistan Government is aimed at protecting the country's rich
biological resources in Karakoram, Hindu Kush and Western
Himalayan mountain ranges, said a UNDP weekly publication.
</P>
<P>
Four protected areas will be created under the project and a
trust fund will be established to sustain conservation activities
well into the future, said the UNDP which spells for the United
Nations Development Program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
