<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNHCR Warn of Another Refugee Crisis in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) Monday warned the international
community of another refugee crisis in Kosovo in the wake of
increasing incidents in the Serb province recently.
</P>
<P>
The return of ethnic Albanians to Kosovo has coincided with the
expulsion, harassment and killing of people of non-Albanian
ethnicity, particularly Serbs and Romas, UNHCR Sadako Ogata told
the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The council met in open session on humanitarian assistance to
refugees. Devoted mostly to African refugee problems, the UNHCR
also touched upon the issue of refugees in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Sadako Ogata said the massacre of 14 Serbs last week is the
latest and most worrying such episode.
</P>
<P>
The international community, which has provided support to
Kosovo Albanians, "could not and must not tolerate that the end of
one refugee crisis overlapped with the beginning of another," she
said.
</P>
<P>
"Retaliation and revenge must not be allowed to prevail," she
added.
</P>
<P>
About 730,000 refugees have returned home since the end of
hostilities and the deployment of international forces in Kosovo
last month, while some 170,000 Serbs from the province have been
displaced recently, according to the number she gave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
