<HEADLINE> Chinese Students Win 2 Gold Medals in Int'l Physical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese middle-school students
won two gold medals in the 30th International Physical Olympic
(IPHO) which ended Monday in the Italian north city of Padova.
</P>
<P>
After passing the exams of theoretical and experimental
physics, which began on July 19 in the University of Padova, Ji
Tao from China's Beijing and Jiang Liang from China's southeast
province of Jiang Su won two of the 30 gold medals, and another
three Chinese students won three silver medals.
</P>
<P>
About 300 students from 60 countries took part in the yearly
worldwide physical competition. Russia's Zravtsov Konstantin won
the golden medal with 49.8 points in the exams (full marks are 50
points), being in the lead among all the participants, and the
Iranian team, with five gold medals in hands, led other countries.
</P>
<P>
The next year's IPHO will be held in Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
