<HEADLINE> Netherlands Sets European Record in 4x100 Freestyle Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch quartet set a European
record on Monday in the men's 4x100 freestyle relay, clocking in 3.
16.26 against the previous mark of 3.16.85 set up by Russia in
1997.
</P>
<P>
In the Atakoy Olympic Natatorium at the 24th European Swimming,
Diving and Synchronized Swiming Championship, the Netherlands thus
took the gold medal in the men's 4x100 freestyle relay with a
record-breaking performance, with Russia finished second in 3.19.
49 and Germany third in 3.20.20.
</P>
<P>
However, Germany triumphed in the women's 4x100 freestyle relay
in 3.40.87, beating Sweden to second in 3.43.07 and Britain third
in 3.43.55.
</P>
<P>
Within expectation, Jose Miguel Gil awarded Spain a gold medal
by winning the men's one-meter springboard with 396.66 points,
while a pair of German divers Andreas Welh and Stefan Ahrens
finished second and third respectively with 395.97 points and 367.
68 points.
</P>
<P>
Russian swimmer Evgueni Bezrouchenko won the men's 5-km open
water race in 59 minutes and 8 seconds. His teammate Alexi Akatiev
finished second and Italian Samuele Pampana placed third.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 400 meter freestyle, British Paul Palmer won the
gold medal in 3.48.12, beating Italian Emiliano Brembilla and
Dragos Coman to second and third.
</P>
<P>
Ukranian Jana Klochkova won the women's medley in 4.38.14.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
