<DOCNO> XIE19990727.0332 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Shows off at Pan Am Walk Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Mexico had a big show-off
at the Pan Am 20km walk race here on Monday as its athletes struck
a pair of golds in the men's and women's events.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Bernardo Segura and the 36-year-old veteran
women athlete M. Mendoza won the titles in an almost similar style,
both toughing out a narrow victory over their Mexican teammates.
</P>
<P>
Segura, crossing the 15km-mark neck-to-neck with his close
rival and fellow Mexican Daniel Garcia, was inspired to a Games
record time of one hour 20 minutes 17 seconds, slashing more than
two minutes off the old mark (1:22:53) set by Ecuardor's Jefferson
Perez four years ago in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Garcia and defending champion Perez, placed the second and
third respectively, broke the tournament's record too, with a time
of 1:20:28 and 1:20:46.
</P>
<P>
Mendoza, pushed from start to finish by her close friend M.
Sanchez, only pulled ahead in the last fading steps, clocking one
hour 34 minutes and 19 seconds. Sanchez followed up with 1:34:46.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal was won by Michelle Rohl of the United States,
whose time was 1:35:22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
