<HEADLINE> Over 1 Million Work From Home in UK: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 1 million people in the
UK are working from home using new information technologies, said
a new report published Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report, by the Institute of Employment Studies, also
forecast that in Britain, about 200,000 people a year will start
teleworking so that they can live and work in the same place.
</P>
<P>
The significant rise in teleworking was the results of many
organizations' decision to release staff from the drudgery of
commuting. Cutting numbers of people in the office also means that
companies can reduce costs through the amount of space they need
to lease.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, many British companies are beginning
to accept the idea of teleworking and there could be advantages
for other types of employees.
</P>
<P>
Disabled people, those who live in remote areas or who need to
stay at home because they have parents or children to look after
could all be employed as teleworkers.
</P>
<P>
However, despite the obvious advantages of not having to go
into the office every day, many people are put off by the thought
of loneliness, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
